      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat and once hot, add the <strong>diced chicken thigh</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until browned</p><p>Once browned, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and cook for a further 2-3 min or until golden</p><p>Meanwhile, combine 1/3 of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>garlic butter</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1695994858601-x200.jpg",
